Adam Langley wrote:
>                epoll_wait(epoll_fd, events, 4, -1);
>                write(1, ".", 1);
The test case is faulty. write will trigger the event again infinitely.
fds 0 and 1 are the same in many cases. Try this:
$ ./epolltest > foo
Now you will only get 1 trigger for each input.
